        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         It's too bad they couldn't add something like what's in Dungeon Seige.  In DS there's a spell that shares the mana pool of every member of the party.  Even characters that don't use mana like tanks and archers will be able to share their mana pool with the rest of the party.</P><P>Basically if it was done in Everquest, warriors, monks and rogues would gain a full mana bar that would go into the party's total mana pool.  If you cast a 240 mana spell, 40 mana would be subtracted from each member of the party instead of it all coming out of your ass.</P><P>I know it sounds confusing but it could have helped even out the imbalance between melee, magic damage and healing/buffing/slowing magic.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
